 of reasons why the goal was unattained, and is even unattainable. The book will be of interest to psychologists, sociologists, professional educators, and students of social change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEducational psychologyxMethodology. 0aLiberalismx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aLiberalismzUnited Statesy20th century. 0aPsychologyxHistoryx20th century. 0aPsychologyxHistoryy20th century. 0aPsychologyxMethodologyxUnited States. 0aPsychologyxMethodology. 0aPsychologyzUnited StatesxMethodology. 0aPsychology. 0aSocial problems. 4aPsychology. 4aSocial Science: Sociology. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Research & Methodology.2bisacsh1 aTravis, L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920899540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889208995423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889208995/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles